{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require courts to allow Victim Witness Statements to be read out in court",
        "additional_details": "I believe the current system is biased towards defendants. I fully agree with a fair and just trial for all defendants, but after going through the process after the murder of my nephew Jay Sewell, I believe the process is one-sided and biased. At closing speeches defence counsel were allowed to read out letters of references as to the characters of defendants, so I believe it would be fair to allow Victim Witness Statements to be heard by the jury.",
        "background": "The Government should pass a law that would require courts to allow Victim Witness Statements to be read out in court with the jury present before they retire to consider the verdict.",
